CAPTIONING MADE POSSIBLE BY
    WARNER BROS., INC.

2
00:05:28,320 --> 00:05:31,490
CLACK, CLACK, STEP
    ABOUT, THE MAID IS HERE.

3
00:05:52,340 --> 00:05:53,810
MAID IS HERE.

4
00:05:53,810 --> 00:05:55,310
COME BACK LATER.

5
00:05:55,310 --> 00:05:57,810
THERE'S NOTHING
FOR YOU TO DO.

6
00:05:57,810 --> 00:06:00,810
BUT YOU GOT YOUR
        "DO NOT DISTURB" SIGN

7
00:06:00,820 --> 00:06:03,820
ON THE DOOR
        FROM MORNING TILL NIGHT.

8
00:06:03,820 --> 00:06:06,820
AT LEAST LET ME
            DRAW THE CURTAINS.

9
00:06:06,820 --> 00:06:08,820
PLEASE DON'T.
JUST LEAVE THEM.

10
00:06:08,820 --> 00:06:11,320
YOU DON'T LIKE
                OUR ISLAND?

11
00:06:11,330 --> 00:06:13,990
HAVEN'T SEEN IT.

12
00:06:17,330 --> 00:06:20,330
EXCUSE ME.
ARE YOU STILL HERE?

13
00:06:20,330 --> 00:06:22,330
YES, MISS.

14
00:06:22,340 --> 00:06:26,340
I HAVE A RAZOR
ON THE TABLE BY THE BED.

15
00:06:26,340 --> 00:06:28,810
COULD YOU BRING IT
TO ME?

16
00:06:28,810 --> 00:06:30,640
YES, MISS.

17
00:06:30,640 --> 00:06:32,980
[HUMMING]

18
00:06:48,330 --> 00:06:50,830
WE FINALLY
MEET FACE TO FACE

19
00:06:50,830 --> 00:06:52,830
WITH YOU
IN THE BATHTUB

20
00:06:52,830 --> 00:06:56,100
WHERE YOU APPEAR
TO HAVE BEEN DEAD.

21
00:06:56,100 --> 00:06:58,830
I DON'T SEE
WHAT DIFFERENCE IT MAKE

22
00:06:58,840 --> 00:07:01,800
IF YOU MISSED
A SPOT OR NOT.

23
00:07:01,800 --> 00:07:03,800
YOU DON'T
LEAVE THE ROOM.

24
00:07:03,810 --> 00:07:05,940
I TELL YOU TRUE,
MISSUS.

25
00:07:05,940 --> 00:07:08,970
YOU GOT TO BUST UP
THE GLOOMY.

26
00:07:10,810 --> 00:07:12,480
THANK YOU.

27
00:07:13,410 --> 00:07:16,310
I ASKED YOU NOT TO OPEN
        THE CURTAINS.

28
00:07:16,320 --> 00:07:17,810
SOMETIME I THINK

29
00:07:17,820 --> 00:07:20,820
I KNOW WHAT'S BEST
FOR OTHER PEOPLE.

30
00:07:20,820 --> 00:07:24,220
IT'S A FLAW I'VE
LEARNED TO LIVE WITH.

31
00:07:25,820 --> 00:07:27,820
I'M HUNGRY.

32
00:07:27,830 --> 00:07:29,830
ARE YOU?

33
00:07:29,830 --> 00:07:33,460
YES. I HAVEN'T EATEN
            A THING ALL DAY.

34
00:07:33,460 --> 00:07:36,800
HOW ABOUT I ORDER YOU UP
SOMETHIN' TO EAT?

35
00:07:36,800 --> 00:07:38,800
WHAT DO YOU THINK?

36
00:07:38,800 --> 00:07:40,470
ALL RIGHT.

37
00:07:43,810 --> 00:07:46,810
YES. THIS IS CLARA MAYFIELD
IN BUNGALOW B.

38
00:07:46,810 --> 00:07:49,810
COULD YOU SEND ME UP
A TRADITIONAL PLATTER

39
00:07:49,810 --> 00:07:51,810
WITH A SIDE
OF CHO CHO?

40
00:07:51,810 --> 00:07:55,310
I GOT A LADY HERE
GREW UP IN JAMAICA

41
00:07:55,320 --> 00:07:57,180
LONGIN' FOR THE TASTE.

42
00:07:57,180 --> 00:07:59,480
CHA, MAN.
THANK YOU.

43
00:08:06,790 --> 00:08:09,460
COME IN NOW.
FOOD IS READY.

44
00:08:13,130 --> 00:08:16,800
IF YOU DON'T LIKE IT,
WE'LL THROW IT AWAY.

45
00:08:16,800 --> 00:08:18,800
YOU'RE ON VACATION.

46
00:08:18,800 --> 00:08:20,800
YOU'RE ALLOWED
A LITTLE CAPRICE.

47
00:08:20,800 --> 00:08:22,800
THAT LOOKS LIKE
                SCRAMBLED EGGS.

48
00:08:22,810 --> 00:08:26,810
NO. YOU MUST TASTE IT FIRST
BEFORE YOU SAY THAT.

49
00:08:26,810 --> 00:08:28,310
THAT'S WONDERFUL.

50
00:08:28,310 --> 00:08:29,810
GOOD CIGAR.

51
00:08:29,810 --> 00:08:32,980
YOU CAN GET IT FRESH
IN PORT ANTONIO.

52
00:08:32,980 --> 00:08:36,050
MAYBE I'LL HIRE A DRIVER
        AND SEE THE TOWN.

53
00:08:36,050 --> 00:08:38,820
DON'T HIRE A DRIVER.
            JUST TAKE THE BUS.

54
00:08:38,820 --> 00:08:41,620
IT RUNS BY THE HOTEL
            EVERY DAY.

55
00:08:41,620 --> 00:08:44,790
YOU NEED YOUR FEET
            AND A FEW CENTS.

56
00:08:44,790 --> 00:08:46,790
I HAVE TO GO.

57
00:08:46,790 --> 00:08:48,290
THANK YOU, CLARA.

58
00:08:48,290 --> 00:08:50,160
YOU'VE BEEN VERY KIND.

59
00:08:50,160 --> 00:08:52,790
IT'S NOT DIFFICULT
            TO BE KIND.

60
00:08:52,800 --> 00:08:56,460
NOW TAKE YOURSELF OUT
        AND BUST UP THE GLOOMY.

61
00:09:31,000 --> 00:09:32,800
EXCUSE ME.

62
00:09:32,800 --> 00:09:33,800
YEAH?

63
00:09:33,800 --> 00:09:35,800
DO YOU KNOW
CLARA MAYFIELD?

64
00:09:35,800 --> 00:09:37,800
SHE LOOKING
    FOR CLARA MAYFIELD.

65
00:09:37,800 --> 00:09:39,170
SHUT YOUR MOUTH.

66
00:09:39,170 --> 00:09:41,810
WHERE DID YOU
                GET HER NAME?

67
00:09:41,810 --> 00:09:44,770
I MET HER
AT MY HOTEL.

68
00:09:44,780 --> 00:09:45,780
MAMA,

69
00:09:45,780 --> 00:09:48,280
THIS LADY DON'T
        KNOW THE SONG.

70
00:09:48,280 --> 00:09:51,650
¶ IN JAMAICA, REMEMBER
    WHEN THE ANGELS FALL ¶

71
00:09:51,650 --> 00:09:54,780
¶ I AS BABYLON,
        BUT MISS CLARA-- ¶

72
00:09:54,790 --> 00:09:56,220
DON'T BE RUDE.

73
00:09:56,220 --> 00:09:58,290
WHAT'S HAPPENED
                TO MISS CLARA

74
00:09:58,290 --> 00:10:00,290
ISN'T THIS
                LADY'S BUSINESS.

75
00:10:00,290 --> 00:10:02,790
IF YOU MUST ASK
                FOR HER,

76
00:10:02,790 --> 00:10:04,960
IT'S BEST TO ASK
                ELSEWHERE.

77
00:10:13,300 --> 00:10:16,800
I WISH I'D KNOWN YOU'D
        BE IN TOWN YESTERDAY.

78
00:10:16,800 --> 00:10:18,800
I WOULD HAVE MET YOU.

79
00:10:18,810 --> 00:10:20,270
NO, REALLY?

80
00:10:20,270 --> 00:10:22,770
HOW MUCH TROUBLE
                COULD IT BE?

81
00:10:22,780 --> 00:10:24,780
WHAT DID YOU DO
YESTERDAY?

82
00:10:24,780 --> 00:10:27,780
I WENT TO CHURCH.
            THEN I CAME HOME,

83
00:10:27,780 --> 00:10:30,780
WROTE LETTERS
                TO MY FRIENDS
                IN BALTIMORE.

84
00:10:30,780 --> 00:10:32,780
WE LIVE JUST OUTSIDE
BALTIMORE.

85
00:10:32,790 --> 00:10:34,280
NO, REALLY?

86
00:10:34,290 --> 00:10:37,290
MY BEST FRIEND OWNS
        A BEAUTY SALON THERE,

87
00:10:37,290 --> 00:10:39,790
AND OTHER FRIENDS
            WORK FOR HER.

88
00:10:39,790 --> 00:10:41,790
SHALL WE HAVE
                OUR TEA?

89
00:10:41,790 --> 00:10:44,790
YOU DON'T MIND
IF THEY SEE YOU?

90
00:10:44,800 --> 00:10:46,800
THEY COULD
                DISCHARGE ME.

91
00:10:46,800 --> 00:10:49,030
I'VE LIVED
                THROUGH WORSE.

92
00:10:49,030 --> 00:10:52,800
YOU'RE MARRIED,
AREN'T YOU, CLARA?

93
00:10:52,800 --> 00:10:54,270
YES.

94
00:10:54,270 --> 00:10:57,440
DOES YOUR HUSBAND
WORK IN TOWN?

95
00:10:58,770 --> 00:11:01,270
I'M SORRY. I'M BEING
TOO INQUISITIVE.

96
00:11:01,280 --> 00:11:03,280
NO, NO. HE WORKS

97
00:11:03,280 --> 00:11:05,280
OUTSIDE THE COUNTRY
            JUST NOW.

98
00:11:05,280 --> 00:11:07,280
SO YOU'RE ALONE
RIGHT NOW?

99
00:11:07,280 --> 00:11:08,780
BY CIRCUMSTANCE.

100
00:11:08,780 --> 00:11:11,780
I NEVER ALLOW MYSELF
        TO GET TOO REGRETFUL.

101
00:11:11,790 --> 00:11:14,290
NOBODY WANTS TO BE
            AROUND SOMEONE

102
00:11:14,290 --> 00:11:16,790
WHO SPREADS
        BLACK CLOUDS AND DOOM.

103
00:11:16,790 --> 00:11:18,960
YOU UNDERSTAND
                WHAT I MEAN.

104
00:11:20,290 --> 00:11:22,290
YES, BUT YOU SEE,

105
00:11:22,290 --> 00:11:25,630
MY BABY DIED
IN HER CRIB RECENTLY.

106
00:11:27,760 --> 00:11:29,760
DIDN'T KNOW
                THE FACT,

107
00:11:29,770 --> 00:11:31,730
BUT I KNEW
                THE SUBSTANCE.

108
00:11:31,730 --> 00:11:36,200
I HAVEN'T BEEN
TERRIBLY RESILIENT.

109
00:11:36,200 --> 00:11:39,540
THAT'LL COME IN TIME.

110
00:11:46,280 --> 00:11:47,950
THANK YOU.

111
00:11:48,780 --> 00:11:51,780
IT'S A FUNNY THING
            ABOUT BEING ALONE.

112
00:11:51,780 --> 00:11:54,280
YOU START TO TALK
            TO YOURSELF.

113
00:11:54,290 --> 00:11:56,290
THEN YOU STOP
                LISTENING,

114
00:11:56,290 --> 00:11:59,390
AND THEN YOU FORGET
            THAT YOU'RE THERE.

115
00:11:59,390 --> 00:12:03,530
I FIND THAT I GET
            INTO SUCH DULLNESS,

116
00:12:03,530 --> 00:12:06,760
BUT YOU LET SOMEBODY
            CALL ME ON THE PHONE

117
00:12:06,760 --> 00:12:08,760
AND TELL ME
            THEIR TROUBLES--

118
00:12:08,770 --> 00:12:11,270
I CAN SAY
        SUCH MARVELOUS THINGS.

119
00:12:11,270 --> 00:12:15,000
THINGS I DON'T KNOW
        WHERE THEY COME FROM

120
00:12:15,010 --> 00:12:18,110
FALL FROM MY LIPS
        LIKE PIECES OF FRUIT,

121
00:12:18,110 --> 00:12:20,780
AND I MUST PAUSE
            TO WONDER

122
00:12:20,780 --> 00:12:23,280
WHO IS IT
            INSIDE OF ME

123
00:12:23,280 --> 00:12:25,610
I DON'T EVEN
            KNOW IS THERE?

124
00:12:25,610 --> 00:12:26,880
LEE?

125
00:12:27,720 --> 00:12:29,450
OH, BILL.

126
00:12:32,290 --> 00:12:35,450
COME MEET THE MOST
WONDERFUL PERSON.

127
00:12:43,760 --> 00:12:45,260
MOM! DAD!

128
00:12:45,260 --> 00:12:47,430
HI. HI.

129
00:12:48,800 --> 00:12:50,260
HOW
                    YOU DOING?

130
00:12:50,270 --> 00:12:52,270
GREAT. I'M GLAD
        YOU'RE BACK.

131
00:12:52,270 --> 00:12:54,270
OLD GLENDA--
        SHE'S THE PITS.

132
00:12:54,270 --> 00:12:56,270
WELL, WE'RE
LETTING HER GO.

133
00:12:56,270 --> 00:12:57,270
REALLY?

134
00:12:57,270 --> 00:12:58,770
YOU GREW.

135
00:12:58,770 --> 00:13:00,770
HOW MANY BAR-UPS
                YOU DOING?

136
00:13:00,780 --> 00:13:02,210
ABOUT FIVE.

137
00:13:02,210 --> 00:13:03,780
LOOKIN' GOOD.

138
00:13:03,780 --> 00:13:05,280
WHO'S THAT?

139
00:13:05,280 --> 00:13:07,250
DAVID,
                THIS IS CLARA.

140
00:13:07,250 --> 00:13:08,750
CLARA'S GOING TO

141
00:13:08,750 --> 00:13:11,750
BE LIVING WITH US
            FROM NOW ON.

142
00:13:11,750 --> 00:13:13,850
HELLO, DAVID.

143
00:13:13,850 --> 00:13:16,750
YOU DON'T GOT TO
BE AFRAID OF ME.

144
00:13:16,760 --> 00:13:18,760
ME NOT GONNA BITE YOU...

145
00:13:18,760 --> 00:13:21,160
UNLESS YOU DON'T BEHAVE.

146
00:13:22,830 --> 00:13:24,260
HERE, CLARA.

147
00:13:24,260 --> 00:13:26,760
NO, THANK YOU.
I GOT IT.

148
00:13:26,760 --> 00:13:29,200
OK, BIG GUY.
        CARRY THIS.

149
00:13:35,770 --> 00:13:37,770
DAD! WHAT'S SHE
                DOING HERE?

150
00:13:37,770 --> 00:13:38,770
SHH!

151
00:13:38,770 --> 00:13:40,740
YOU DIDN'T SAY
                ANYTHING!

152
00:13:40,740 --> 00:13:44,410
YOUR MOTHER JUST NEEDS
SOME HELP, DAVID.

153
00:13:48,710 --> 00:13:51,750
YOU'LL HAVE STRANGERS
TAKE CARE OF ME NOW

154
00:13:51,750 --> 00:13:53,750
SO YOU DON'T
HAVE TO!

155
00:13:53,750 --> 00:13:55,250
WHAT IS THIS?

156
00:13:55,250 --> 00:13:57,190
JUST TAKE IT
        EASY, DAVID.

157
00:13:57,190 --> 00:13:59,090
I UNDERSTAND
                THE LITTLE BOY.

158
00:13:59,090 --> 00:14:02,260
YOU DON'T UNDERSTAND.
I'LL MAKE YOU LEAVE.

159
00:14:02,260 --> 00:14:03,590
STOP IT!

160
00:14:03,590 --> 00:14:05,090
IT'S ALL RIGHT.

161
00:14:05,090 --> 00:14:06,260
LISTEN.

162
00:14:06,260 --> 00:14:09,930
NOBODY MAKES ME DO
        NOTHIN' I DON'T WANT TO,

163
00:14:09,930 --> 00:14:12,760
SO AIM THAT MEANNESS
    AND NASTY TALK ELSEWHERE.

164
00:14:12,770 --> 00:14:14,730
YOU GOT ANOTHER
        THING COMING

165
00:14:14,730 --> 00:14:18,100
IF YOU THINK YOU'LL ACT
    SO DREADFUL AROUND CLARA.

166
00:14:19,740 --> 00:14:21,900
COME THIS WAY,
            CLARA.

167
00:14:26,240 --> 00:14:28,240
WHERE ARE YOU
TAKING HER?

168
00:14:28,240 --> 00:14:29,910
LEE?

169
00:14:54,730 --> 00:14:57,230
WELL, COME UP
        IF YOU MUST.

170
00:14:57,240 --> 00:15:00,400
DON'T STAND DOWN THERE
    MARAUDING LIKE A SPY.

171
00:15:17,020 --> 00:15:18,250
YOU'RE OUR MAID.

172
00:15:18,250 --> 00:15:21,720
THIS IS A GUEST ROOM--
A ROOM FOR GUESTS.

173
00:15:21,720 --> 00:15:24,730
PERHAPS YOUR MOTHER
            WANT ME CLOSE TO YOU

174
00:15:24,730 --> 00:15:27,230
SO I CAN CHANGE
                YOUR DIAPERS.

175
00:15:27,230 --> 00:15:28,760
VERY FUNNY.

176
00:15:28,760 --> 00:15:31,530
HOW COME YOU TALK
SO WEIRD?

177
00:15:31,530 --> 00:15:34,230
YOU AIN'T HEARD WEIRD
        TALKIN' YET, CHILD.

178
00:15:34,230 --> 00:15:37,740
I TALK SO BAD YOU'LL
        THINK IT'S A NIGHTMARE.

179
00:15:37,740 --> 00:15:39,240
WHAT'S THAT MEAN?

180
00:15:39,240 --> 00:15:42,770
DON'T ACT PROPER, I'LL
        TURN YOU INTO A TOAD.

181
00:15:42,770 --> 00:15:45,710
OOH. YOU'RE SOME KIND
OF WITCH, OR WHAT?

182
00:15:45,710 --> 00:15:47,440
SOMETHING LIKE THAT,
            YEAH.

183
00:15:47,450 --> 00:15:49,310
YOU'RE NOT IN CHARGE.

184
00:15:49,310 --> 00:15:52,150
I WANT YOU TO KNOW
AT THE START.

185
00:15:52,150 --> 00:15:56,220
THAT IS OBVIOUS,
                SO WE MOVE ON
                TO OTHER THINGS.

186
00:15:56,220 --> 00:15:58,220
SHE'S NOT WELL--
MY MOTHER.

187
00:15:58,220 --> 00:16:00,590
YOU DON'T SEEM
        TOO HEALTHY YOURSELF.

188
00:16:00,590 --> 00:16:02,360
YOU'RE A JERK.

189
00:16:02,360 --> 00:16:05,220
WELL, IF I'M A JERK,
            YOU'RE A BOBO.

190
00:16:05,230 --> 00:16:07,190
THEN YOU'RE
A SUPER-DWEEB.

191
00:16:07,200 --> 00:16:10,830
IF I AM A SUPER-DWEEB,
        YOU ARE A BUBU-YAGA.

192
00:16:10,830 --> 00:16:12,830
DON'T SAY
                ANYTHING ELSE.

193
00:16:12,830 --> 00:16:14,830
BEST YOU AND ME,

194
00:16:14,840 --> 00:16:17,840
WE LEARN TO BECOME
            PART OF ONE ANOTHER.

195
00:16:17,840 --> 00:16:20,840
PERHAPS THEN THERE
            IS SOME HOPE FOR US.

196
00:16:20,840 --> 00:16:22,840
LISTEN,
WHAT CAN I SAY?

197
00:16:22,840 --> 00:16:25,840
I'M SORRY, BUT YOU'RE
NOT WINNING ME OVER.

198
00:16:25,850 --> 00:16:28,810
THAT'S THE BEST
            I CAN DO FOR TODAY,

199
00:16:28,820 --> 00:16:31,980
SO JUST TAKE YOURSELF
        OUT OF HERE. GOOD-BYE.

200
00:17:49,330 --> 00:17:52,490
GET YOUR DIRTY HANDS
OUT OF THERE.

201
00:17:53,730 --> 00:17:56,430
I HOPE THEY LIKE
            HIYAKI

202
00:17:56,430 --> 00:17:58,330
AS MUCH AS I DO.

203
00:17:58,330 --> 00:18:00,830
IT STRONGLY RESEMBLES
BABY PUKE.

204
00:18:00,840 --> 00:18:03,840
IT'S GOT SOME OF THAT
        IN IT, ABSOLUTELY.

205
00:18:03,840 --> 00:18:05,840
MY, BUT YOU'RE
        OBSERVANT.

206
00:18:05,840 --> 00:18:08,810
I LEFT SOME TOTOS
            IN THE OVEN

207
00:18:08,810 --> 00:18:10,810
FOR THE LITTLE BOY.

208
00:18:10,810 --> 00:18:12,540
I'M NOT
A LITTLE BOY.

209
00:18:12,550 --> 00:18:15,810
YOU ACT LIKE ONE.
            I GOT ALL CONFUSED.

210
00:18:15,820 --> 00:18:17,820
SHIRTS.
        I NEED SHIRTS.

211
00:18:17,820 --> 00:18:19,920
WHAT DO YOU
                    CALL THOSE?

212
00:18:19,920 --> 00:18:21,820
WHERE ARE YOU
            GOING?

213
00:18:21,820 --> 00:18:22,920
VANCOUVER.

214
00:18:22,920 --> 00:18:23,920
HOW COME?

215
00:18:23,920 --> 00:18:25,960
TO SETTLE THE WORLD'S
MARITIME CRISES.

216
00:18:25,960 --> 00:18:27,260
THEY'RE NOT STARCHED.

217
00:18:27,260 --> 00:18:29,460
NO, OF COURSE NOT.

218
00:18:29,460 --> 00:18:31,330
LEONA, DIDN'T
YOU TELL HER

219
00:18:31,330 --> 00:18:33,830
I LIKE MY SHIRTS
LIGHTLY STARCHED?

220
00:18:33,830 --> 00:18:35,830
SHE DELIVERED ME
            THE LIST

221
00:18:35,830 --> 00:18:37,830
OF EVERYBODY'S
            FAKEY-FAKEY HABITS.

222
00:18:37,830 --> 00:18:40,300
I EXPLAINED STARCH
            RUINS YOUR SHIRTS.

223
00:18:40,300 --> 00:18:41,800
IT DOESN'T.

224
00:18:41,800 --> 00:18:45,040
IF IT DOES,
I'LL GET NEW ONES.

225
00:18:45,040 --> 00:18:48,810
MR. HART, YOU LET ME
        SHOW YOU A GOOD IRONING

226
00:18:48,810 --> 00:18:50,810
GIVES THE FEEL
                OF STARCH.

227
00:18:50,810 --> 00:18:53,810
THE MONEY YOU SAVE
            ON THOSE NICE SHIRTS

228
00:18:53,810 --> 00:18:56,310
YOU CAN SPEND
                ON GOLF BALLS.

229
00:18:56,320 --> 00:18:58,220
FINE.

230
00:18:58,220 --> 00:18:59,820
TASTE?

231
00:18:59,820 --> 00:19:01,780
NO, THANKS.

232
00:19:04,290 --> 00:19:06,290
[HUMMING]

233
00:19:06,290 --> 00:19:08,620
AND WHAT ARE THOSE?

234
00:19:08,630 --> 00:19:10,320
TOTOS. COCONUT
                RAISIN COOKIES.

235
00:19:10,330 --> 00:19:12,330
I MADE THEM
                FOR YOU.

236
00:19:12,330 --> 00:19:14,430
THAT'S VERY KIND
OF YOU,

237
00:19:14,430 --> 00:19:16,300
BUT I RARELY
EAT SWEETS,

238
00:19:16,300 --> 00:19:18,300
AND DAVID SHOULDN'T
HAVE ANY.

239
00:19:18,300 --> 00:19:20,800
HE'S TRAINING
FOR THE SWIM TEAM.

