00:54:37,920 --> 00:54:40,420
HOW ABOUT SCAMPI?
YOU LOVE SHRIMP.

716
00:54:40,420 --> 00:54:41,920
FINE.

717
00:54:46,090 --> 00:54:48,220
CIAO, BILL.

718
00:54:48,220 --> 00:54:49,720
HI.

719
00:54:50,890 --> 00:54:52,720
HI.

720
00:54:52,730 --> 00:54:55,230
DAVID, MEET CATHERINE,
MY DECORATOR.

721
00:54:55,230 --> 00:54:58,330
CATHERINE, THIS IS
MY SON, DAVID HART.

722
00:54:58,330 --> 00:55:00,400
HELLO, DAVID HART.

723
00:55:02,230 --> 00:55:05,230
HOW ABOUT HAVING
SOME LUNCH WITH US?

724
00:55:05,240 --> 00:55:07,400
I'LL JUST STAY
        A MINUTE.

725
00:55:16,250 --> 00:55:18,750
UM, DAVID, WHAT
        DO YOU THINK

726
00:55:18,750 --> 00:55:20,750
OF YOUR FATHER'S
        APARTMENT?

727
00:55:20,750 --> 00:55:23,950
IT'S PRETTY GOD DAMN
            OSTENTATIOUS.

728
00:55:23,950 --> 00:55:26,720
OF COURSE, THAT'S JUST
        A KID'S OPINION.

729
00:55:26,720 --> 00:55:29,720
I MEAN, I DON'T
            EVEN SPEAK ITALIAN.

730
00:55:29,720 --> 00:55:33,730
ARE YOU
            SEXUALLY INVOLVED
            WITH MY FATHER?

731
00:55:33,730 --> 00:55:35,730
SON, DON'T BE SHY.

732
00:55:35,730 --> 00:55:39,060
JUST JUMP IN.
ASK WHATEVER YOU NEED TO.

733
00:55:39,070 --> 00:55:40,900
ARE YOU?

734
00:55:40,900 --> 00:55:42,970
YES, I AM.

735
00:55:46,840 --> 00:55:50,270
I CARE
    ABOUT YOUR DAD A LOT.

736
00:55:54,480 --> 00:55:56,310
WELL,
        ENJOY YOUR LUNCH.

737
00:55:56,310 --> 00:55:59,480
IT WAS NICE
        TO MEET YOU, DAVID.

738
00:56:00,820 --> 00:56:02,320
BYE.

739
00:56:02,320 --> 00:56:04,320
I'LL SEE YOU LATER.

740
00:56:04,320 --> 00:56:05,990
BYE.

741
00:56:07,890 --> 00:56:11,560
SHE REALLY LIKES YOU,
        DOESN'T SHE?

742
00:56:11,560 --> 00:56:14,490
WHY NOT? I'M NOT
SUCH A BAD GUY.

743
00:56:14,490 --> 00:56:16,830
YOU AND MOM
            JUST GOT SEPARATED,

744
00:56:16,830 --> 00:56:19,260
AND YOU ALREADY HAVE
            SOMEONE ELSE.

745
00:56:19,260 --> 00:56:22,330
AT LEAST I'M NOT HIDING
WHO I'M SEEING.

746
00:56:22,330 --> 00:56:25,770
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?
            WHO'S MOM SEEING?

747
00:56:25,770 --> 00:56:27,670
THE GREAT SINGING
PSYCHOLOGIST

748
00:56:27,670 --> 00:56:29,540
WE MET THAT SATURDAY.

749
00:56:29,540 --> 00:56:31,570
THAT DR. EPSTEIN GUY?

750
00:56:31,570 --> 00:56:33,470
IT'S GOOD, DAVID.

751
00:56:33,470 --> 00:56:36,810
YOUR MOM DESERVES
TO BE HAPPY, TOO.

752
00:56:36,810 --> 00:56:39,810
SO IN OTHER WORDS,
            YOU AND MOM...

753
00:56:39,810 --> 00:56:43,980
YOU AND MOM
            DESERVE TO BE HAPPY.

754
00:56:43,980 --> 00:56:47,480
SOUNDS RIGHT.
            MAKES SENSE.

755
00:56:50,250 --> 00:56:53,990
HE HAD NO RIGHT
        TO TELL YOU THAT.

756
00:56:53,990 --> 00:56:56,920
WHEN WOULD YOU HAVE
GOTTEN AROUND TO TELLING ME?

757
00:56:56,930 --> 00:56:58,830
WHEN I FIGURED OUT

758
00:56:58,830 --> 00:57:02,160
HOW I WANTED TO
        EXPLAIN IT TO YOU.

759
00:57:09,300 --> 00:57:11,940
COME HERE, BABY.

760
00:57:19,810 --> 00:57:22,310
PETER'S MAKING
                A LOT OF THINGS

761
00:57:22,310 --> 00:57:24,310
FALL INTO PLACE
                FOR ME.

762
00:57:24,310 --> 00:57:28,320
I FEEL JUST NOW
                I HAVE TO PUT
                ALL MY ENERGY

763
00:57:28,320 --> 00:57:30,320
INTO HELPING MYSELF

764
00:57:30,320 --> 00:57:32,820
BEFORE I CAN HELP
            ANYONE ELSE.

765
00:57:32,820 --> 00:57:35,290
I KNOW THAT SOUNDS
            REALLY SELFISH,

766
00:57:35,290 --> 00:57:38,460
BUT I'M DOING
                THE BEST I CAN.

767
00:57:41,130 --> 00:57:43,460
AND I LOVE YOU.

768
00:57:44,630 --> 00:57:46,460
I DO.

769
00:57:47,800 --> 00:57:49,800
KISS.

770
00:57:49,800 --> 00:57:51,630
[CAR DOOR SLAMS]

771
00:57:57,810 --> 00:58:00,440
HI. HOW WAS
                YOUR WEEKEND?

772
00:58:00,440 --> 00:58:03,810
OH, CHILD,
            IT WAS WONDERFUL.

773
00:58:03,810 --> 00:58:05,310
GOOD LAVISHING.

774
00:58:05,310 --> 00:58:08,780
WE GIRLS
            CAN CERTAINLY CHAT.

775
00:58:08,780 --> 00:58:10,280
WOO!

776
00:58:10,280 --> 00:58:11,950
WHO CAME OVER?

777
00:58:11,950 --> 00:58:14,950
IT WAS ME, BLANCHE,
        LYDIA, AND BOBS,

778
00:58:14,950 --> 00:58:18,290
AND THE GIRLS WANTED
        ME TO TELL YOU HI.

779
00:58:18,290 --> 00:58:21,290
BLANCHE DID YOU UP
IN SOME PINKIE HAIRDO?

780
00:58:21,290 --> 00:58:24,290
IT BE LOOKIN'
VERY NICE ON YOU.

781
00:58:24,300 --> 00:58:27,300
AREN'T YOU
            THE SILVER-TONGUED
            DEVIL.

782
00:58:27,300 --> 00:58:30,000
HOW WAS IT
            AT YOUR FATHER'S?

783
00:58:30,000 --> 00:58:31,970
TERRIFIC.
REALLY MEMORABLE.

784
00:58:31,970 --> 00:58:33,970
AREN'T THEY SUPPOSED TO

785
00:58:33,970 --> 00:58:35,970
KEEP UP APPEARANCES
OR SOMETHING

786
00:58:35,970 --> 00:58:37,970
FOR A CHILD'S BENEFIT?

787
00:58:37,980 --> 00:58:41,280
AND MAKE IT LOOK LIKE
    THEY'LL GET BACK TOGETHER?

788
00:58:41,280 --> 00:58:43,280
DAVID, CLARA,
I'M LEAVING.

789
00:58:43,280 --> 00:58:44,780
WHERE TO?

790
00:58:44,780 --> 00:58:46,780
PETER HAS
A WORKSHOP TONIGHT.

791
00:58:46,780 --> 00:58:49,950
I'M LATE. I'LL TALK
TO YOU LATER.

792
00:58:56,960 --> 00:59:00,560
OH! MY TWO-CENT TOOTSIES
        ARE KILLING ME.

793
00:59:00,560 --> 00:59:03,800
HERE, LET ME
RUB THEM FOR YOU.

794
00:59:09,140 --> 00:59:10,970
THANK YOU.

795
00:59:14,310 --> 00:59:16,770
WHAT'S IN THAT
RED SUITCASE?

796
00:59:16,780 --> 00:59:18,780
WHAT RED SUITCASE?

797
00:59:18,780 --> 00:59:21,780
THAT ONE YOU KEEP
UNDER YOUR BED

798
00:59:21,780 --> 00:59:23,780
AND TAKE
TO YOUR APARTMENT.

799
00:59:23,780 --> 00:59:25,780
NONE OF YOUR BUSINESS.

800
00:59:25,780 --> 00:59:28,080
MY ROOM
            IS ME PRIVACY.

801
00:59:28,090 --> 00:59:30,450
HOW WAS IT
            AT YOUR DAD'S?

802
00:59:30,460 --> 00:59:33,490
HOW COME YOU DON'T
HAVE HAIR ON YOUR LEGS?

803
00:59:33,490 --> 00:59:35,890
BECAUSE I'M
            NATURALLY HAIRLESS.

804
00:59:35,890 --> 00:59:38,330
HOW WAS IT
                AT YOUR DAD'S?

805
00:59:38,330 --> 00:59:40,800
WHY YOU TOUCH ME
                LIKE THAT?

806
00:59:40,800 --> 00:59:42,530
LIKE HOW?

807
00:59:42,530 --> 00:59:45,870
DON'T YOU NEVER
            TOUCH ME LIKE THAT
            AGAIN.

808
00:59:45,870 --> 00:59:47,330
I'M SORRY.

809
00:59:47,340 --> 00:59:50,300
KEEP YOUR HANDS
        OFF MY PERSON, CHILD.

810
00:59:50,310 --> 00:59:51,770
WAIT.

811
00:59:51,770 --> 00:59:53,940
GET OUT,
            NOW! GET OUT!

812
00:59:59,850 --> 01:00:01,780
[DOOR OPENS]

813
01:00:11,060 --> 01:00:14,790
YOUR DINNER'S DOWNSTAIRS.
YOU'D BETTER GO AND EAT.

814
01:00:15,790 --> 01:00:17,790
I'M NOT HUNGRY.

815
01:00:19,060 --> 01:00:21,160
YOU MUST
KEEP UP YOUR STRENGTH.

816
01:00:21,160 --> 01:00:24,100
I'LL ALWAYS JUST BE
            A PUNY MIDGET.

817
01:00:24,100 --> 01:00:27,530
I GUESS I'M SUPPOSED
TO FEEL SORRY FOR YOU.

818
01:00:27,540 --> 01:00:30,440
BUT I'LL TELL YOU
IN MY COUNTRY

819
01:00:30,440 --> 01:00:34,440
"PUNY PUNY" MEANS MEN
WITH MANY WOMEN
AND LOTS OF LAND.

820
01:00:34,440 --> 01:00:36,440
I SHOULD MOVE THERE.

821
01:00:36,440 --> 01:00:39,940
NO. YOU NEED TO LEARN
HOW TO LIVE HERE,

822
01:00:39,950 --> 01:00:41,950
BUT YOU MUST ALSO LEARN

823
01:00:41,950 --> 01:00:45,620
NOT TO TOUCH A LADY
UNLESS YOU'VE BEEN INVITED.

824
01:00:47,790 --> 01:00:49,120
CLARA?

825
01:00:50,590 --> 01:00:52,420
YES, DAVID?

826
01:00:53,590 --> 01:00:57,460
WHY DID EDITH
            HAVE TO DIE AND
            MESS UP EVERYTHING?

827
01:01:00,760 --> 01:01:02,260
THEM THAT DIE

828
01:01:02,260 --> 01:01:06,330
DON'T CREATE THE AGONY
AND STRANGENESS OF LIFE, DAVID.

829
01:01:06,330 --> 01:01:08,500
ONLY THE LIVING DO THAT.

830
01:01:11,610 --> 01:01:14,040
I FIGURED
            YOU'D SAY THAT.

831
01:01:14,040 --> 01:01:16,270
THEN WHY YOU ASK ME?

832
01:01:20,110 --> 01:01:21,610
DAVID.

833
01:01:24,920 --> 01:01:28,120
DAVID, LOOK UPON ME.

834
01:01:30,250 --> 01:01:36,420
KNOW THIS--
YOU CAN DEPEND ON ME.

835
01:01:37,760 --> 01:01:39,420
ALWAYS?

836
01:01:40,760 --> 01:01:44,930
ALWAYS IS MUCH LONGER
THAN YOU'RE GOING TO NEED ME.

837
01:02:03,580 --> 01:02:05,080
I DON'T GET IT.

838
01:02:05,080 --> 01:02:08,580
THE GUY KEEPS ROLLING
THE BOULDER UP THE MOUNTAIN

839
01:02:08,590 --> 01:02:11,590
EVEN THOUGH HE KNOWS
IT'LL ROLL BACK DOWN.

840
01:02:11,590 --> 01:02:14,590
SISYPHUS IS CONDEMNED
    TO ROLL THE BOULDER.

841
01:02:14,590 --> 01:02:16,590
HE HAS NO CHOICE,

842
01:02:16,590 --> 01:02:19,590
BUT HE COMMITS
    EVERY FIBER OF HIS BEING

843
01:02:19,600 --> 01:02:21,100
TO THE ENTERPRISE.

844
01:02:21,100 --> 01:02:23,100
IT'S STUPID.
HE'S AN IDIOT.

845
01:02:23,100 --> 01:02:25,100
BECAUSE IT'S THE EFFORT,
            DAVID,

846
01:02:25,100 --> 01:02:28,300
THAT GIVES MEANING
        TO OUR LIVES.

847
01:02:28,300 --> 01:02:29,800
IS THAT RIGHT?

848
01:02:29,810 --> 01:02:31,270
YEP.

849
01:02:31,270 --> 01:02:33,770
YOU MAKE
ALL THIS STUFF UP?

850
01:02:33,780 --> 01:02:36,240
NO. A FRENCH WRITER
            NAMED CAMUS.

851
01:02:36,240 --> 01:02:38,840
I JUST STOLE IT.

852
01:02:42,080 --> 01:02:45,080
UH, I'M GOING TO
            LEAVE YOU GUYS

853
01:02:45,090 --> 01:02:47,550
AND GO CHECK
            ON MY SERVICE.

854
01:02:47,550 --> 01:02:50,590
USE THE PHONE
        IN THE LIVING ROOM.

855
01:02:50,590 --> 01:02:52,760
YOU'LL HAVE
            MORE PRIVACY.

856
01:02:58,060 --> 01:03:00,100
DAVID, PETER
            HAS ASKED ME

857
01:03:00,100 --> 01:03:02,600
TO HELP HIM
            ON A WORKSHOP

858
01:03:02,600 --> 01:03:04,570
THIS WEEKEND
            IN SAN FRANCISCO.

859
01:03:04,570 --> 01:03:06,570
NOW, I TOLD HIM

860
01:03:06,570 --> 01:03:10,070
THAT I WOULD
            SPEAK TO YOU
            ABOUT IT FIRST,

861
01:03:10,070 --> 01:03:12,570
THAT IF
            IT BOTHERED YOU
            TERRIBLY,

862
01:03:12,570 --> 01:03:14,570
I WOULDN'T DO IT.

863
01:03:15,580 --> 01:03:17,580
SURE. GO.

864
01:03:36,100 --> 01:03:37,930
[TELEPHONE RINGS]

865
01:03:41,400 --> 01:03:42,730
HELLO?

866
01:03:43,570 --> 01:03:46,070
OH. NO, MOM'S
        NOT HERE, DAD.

867
01:03:46,070 --> 01:03:49,070
SHE IS SACKING OUT
        IN SAN FRANCISCO

868
01:03:49,070 --> 01:03:51,310
WITH THE OLD
    SINGING PSYCHOLOGIST.

869
01:03:52,140 --> 01:03:56,280
YEAH. SHE WENT TO HELP HIM
        RUN A WORKSHOP.

870
01:03:56,280 --> 01:03:59,580
YEAH. THAT'S THE WORD HERE, DAD.
        FILM AT 6:00.

871
01:03:59,580 --> 01:04:02,080
I'M JUST HANGING OUT
        WITH CLARA,

872
01:04:02,080 --> 01:04:04,580
SITTING IN FRONT
        OF MOTHER'S MIRROR

873
01:04:04,590 --> 01:04:07,250
AND PUTTING ON
    THAT WOMAN'S COSMETICS,

874
01:04:07,260 --> 01:04:09,760
SO TALKIE-TALKIE
        NEXT WEEK, FATHER.

875
01:04:09,760 --> 01:04:11,760
SO LONG, NOW.

876
01:04:32,080 --> 01:04:36,250
YOU KNOW SHE NOT WANT YOU
    TO TROUBLE HER THINGS.

877
01:04:37,750 --> 01:04:40,420
ME NOT TROUBLE
HER THINGS.

878
01:04:48,660 --> 01:04:50,820
COME ON. SIT UP.

879
01:05:04,570 --> 01:05:05,570
CLARA.

880
01:05:05,570 --> 01:05:07,740
THAT IS MY NAME.

881
01:05:09,240 --> 01:05:12,410
WILL I BE LIKE--
LIKE<i> YOUR</i> SON NOW?</i>

882
01:05:15,080 --> 01:05:18,050
I MEAN,
 I<i> AM</i> YOUR FRIEND
 AND EVERYTHING.</i>

883
01:05:18,050 --> 01:05:19,720
BUT OF COURSE.

884
01:05:21,220 --> 01:05:23,050
BUT, DAVID,

885
01:05:23,050 --> 01:05:26,890
DON'T
            THE LITTLE GIRLS
            INTEREST YOU YET?

886
01:05:27,890 --> 01:05:30,890
IT'S NOT THAT
THEY DON'T INTEREST ME.

887
01:05:30,890 --> 01:05:33,060
I JUST DON'T
INTEREST THEM.

888
01:05:33,900 --> 01:05:35,060
OH.

889
01:05:37,230 --> 01:05:39,400
WELL, SOMETHING
            TELLS ME

890
01:05:39,400 --> 01:05:41,570
THAT VERY, VERY SOON

891
01:05:41,570 --> 01:05:46,240
THOSE LITTLE GIRLS
        ARE GOING TO BE
        INTERESTED IN YOU, TOO.

892
01:05:47,670 --> 01:05:49,170
YOU SWEAR?

893
01:05:49,170 --> 01:05:51,340
ABSOLUTELY.

894
01:05:53,810 --> 01:05:56,310
WHAT A STRANGE CHILD
            YOU ARE.

895
01:05:56,310 --> 01:05:59,310
SOMETIME YOU FEEL
            SO STRANGE TO ME

896
01:05:59,320 --> 01:06:02,320
I THINK I DON'T
            KNOW YOU AT ALL.

897
01:06:02,320 --> 01:06:04,320
OF COURSE
YOU KNOW ME.

898
01:06:04,320 --> 01:06:06,820
YOU KNOW ME
BETTER THAN ANYONE.

899
01:06:06,820 --> 01:06:08,820
NOT TRUE.

900
01:06:09,660 --> 01:06:12,990
NOBODY EVER
            REALLY KNOWS ANYONE,

901
01:06:12,990 --> 01:06:16,000
AND JUST WHEN
            YOU THINK YOU DO,

902
01:06:16,000 --> 01:06:20,170
PEOPLE CHANGE RIGHT
            BEFORE YOUR EYES.

903
01:06:27,810 --> 01:06:30,310
<i> ¶ I HOPE</i>
    <i> YOU LIKE JAMMIN', TOO ¶</i></i>

904
01:06:30,310 --> 01:06:32,310
4, 5, 6.

905
01:06:32,310 --> 01:06:34,240
7, 8, 9.

906
01:06:34,250 --> 01:06:35,650
7, 8.

907
01:06:35,650 --> 01:06:36,810
7. 8.

908
01:06:36,810 --> 01:06:39,480
1, 2, 3.

909
01:06:42,650 --> 01:06:46,790
<i> ¶ JAMMIN' TILL</i>
    <i> THE JAM IS THROUGH ¶</i></i>

910
01:06:46,790 --> 01:06:48,320
SO, CLARA'S BOY,

911
01:06:48,320 --> 01:06:51,720
YOU MUSTN'T BE
            FRIGHTENED OF ME.

912
01:06:51,730 --> 01:06:55,660
MUST BE CLARA
            TELL YOU SOME
            BAD THINGS ABOUT ME.

913
01:06:55,660 --> 01:06:57,630
I'M NOT SCARED OF YOU.

914
01:06:57,630 --> 01:07:00,130
SHE DIDN'T SAY ANYTHING
ABOUT YOU.

915
01:07:00,130 --> 01:07:03,130
ALL YOU NEED
            TO KNOW, THEN,
            IS THIS--

916
01:07:03,130 --> 01:07:06,640
WHEN MAYFIELD GO,
            DEATH AND ALL
            BE A-FOLLOW.

917
01:07:06,640 --> 01:07:09,540
I'LL GO UPSTAIRS
AND MAKE SOME KOOL-AID.

918
01:07:09,540 --> 01:07:12,470
DON'T MOVE YET.
            JUST STAY
            RIGHT HERE.

919
01:07:12,480 --> 01:07:15,480
WHAT THE HECK.
I'VE GOT SOME TIME.

920
01:07:15,480 --> 01:07:17,480
SO TELL ME
            SOMETHING.

921
01:07:17,480 --> 01:07:19,980
DID SHE TELL YOU
            ABOUT RALPHIE?

922
01:07:19,980 --> 01:07:22,480
I KNOW
            SHE NO TELL YOU.

923
01:07:22,480 --> 01:07:23,980
YEAH? SHE DID.

924
01:07:23,990 --> 01:07:26,990
SHE COULDN'T
            TELL YOU
            THE WHOLE STORY.

925
01:07:26,990 --> 01:07:29,490
WHAT DO YOU CARE
ANYWAY, HUH?

926
01:07:29,490 --> 01:07:32,660
ME HAVE ME REASONS
            FOR CARE.

927
01:07:36,460 --> 01:07:40,630
YOU ASK ABOUT RALPHIE.
MAKE CERTAIN YOU DO THAT, MAN.

928
01:08:26,810 --> 01:08:29,310
WELCOME, CLARA.

929
01:08:50,470 --> 01:08:51,460
YOU...

930
01:08:51,470 --> 01:08:53,970
THEY TOLD ME
            YOU WAS OUTSIDE.

931
01:08:53,970 --> 01:08:55,470
I HAD TO.

932
01:08:55,470 --> 01:08:56,470
WHY?

933
01:08:56,470 --> 01:08:58,970
IT WAS BURNING UP
IN HERE.

934
01:08:58,970 --> 01:09:01,470
I'M NOT USED
TO THE TROPICS.

935
01:09:01,470 --> 01:09:04,480
THEN DORA COME BY
            WITH HER FRIEND.

936
01:09:04,480 --> 01:09:07,540
SHE WAS TRYING
TO JUKE ME UP.

937
01:09:07,550 --> 01:09:09,980
JUST WHAT DID DORA
            TELL YOU?

938
01:09:09,980 --> 01:09:11,980
TO ASK YOU
ABOUT RALPHIE.

939
01:09:11,980 --> 01:09:15,450
WHAT DID I SAY
            ABOUT ASKING
            ABOUT MY PERSON?

940
01:09:15,450 --> 01:09:17,150
I DIDN'T SAY
ANYTHING.

941
01:09:17,150 --> 01:09:19,250
SHE SAY
            ANYTHING ELSE?

942
01:09:19,260 --> 01:09:21,260
NOTHING.

943
01:09:22,790 --> 01:09:24,960
THAT'S IT.
I SWEAR.

944
01:09:43,810 --> 01:09:45,010
CLARA?

945
01:09:45,010 --> 01:09:47,110
YES, DAVID?

946
01:09:51,950 --> 01:09:53,620
NOTHING.

947
01:09:59,120 --> 01:10:06,390
¶ GOD HAS SMILED ON ME ¶

948
01:10:06,400 --> 01:10:13,000
¶ HE HAS SET ME FREE ¶

